This is supported via the web-streams interface on `Deno.Conn` together with `AbortSignal`. `conn.readable` is a `ReadableStream`, so you can abort a pending read with a timeout:

```ts
// Abort the read after N ms
await conn.readable.pipeTo(dest, { signal: AbortSignal.timeout(N) });
```

Or with a reader you control:

```ts
const reader = conn.readable.getReader();
const ac = new AbortController();
const timer = setTimeout(() => ac.abort(), N);
try {
  const { value } = await Promise.race([
    reader.read(),
    new Promise((_, rej) =>
      ac.signal.addEventListener("abort", () =>
        rej(new DOMException("aborted", "AbortError")))),
  ]);
  // process `value`
} catch (e) {
  if (e.name === "AbortError") await reader.cancel();
} finally {
  clearTimeout(timer);
}
```

Both abort a read that is waiting on a socket with no incoming data. Closing as resolved — the abortable read this issue asked for is available through `conn.readable` + `AbortSignal`.

