Closing as by-design.

Permission prompts are intentionally disabled for `deno test` and `deno bench` — both force `--no-prompt` at parse time:

```rust
// NOTE: `deno test` always uses `--no-prompt`, tests shouldn't ever do
// interactive prompts, unless done by user code
flags.permissions.no_prompt = true;
```

(`cli/args/flags.rs`, in both the test and bench arg parsers.) A missing permission in a test fails fast rather than prompting, which is the desired behavior for a non-interactive run.

The original re-prompting report was traced by the OP to their own code, and the follow-up about `--prompt` no longer applies: `--prompt` is overridden for test/bench, so the only way a prompt happens is user code calling `Deno.permissions.request()` directly, and those grants are scoped per test module by design (isolation), not a bug. Nothing here describes currently broken behavior, so closing.

