That's because it's a floating promise rejection, which we don't support this for. https://deno.land/std@0.137.0/http/server_test.ts#L680 This happens because there is another awaited async operation before `servePromise` is eventually awaited. We fix that in the test with
```diff
  Deno.test(`serve listens on the port 8000 by default`, async () => {
    const url = "http://localhost:8000";
    const body = "Hello from port 8000";

    const handler = () => new Response(body);
    const abortController = new AbortController();

    const servePromise = serve(handler, {
      signal: abortController.signal,
    });
+   servePromise.catch(() => {});

    try {
      const response = await fetch(url);
      assertEquals(await response.text(), body);
    } finally {
      abortController.abort();
      await servePromise;
    }
  });
```

