@cmoog your proposal is close to something we recently implemented. I don't think we would want to use `filter()` to just drop arguments though, as that could lead to unexpected behavior. For example, in the case of `wrangler` here, I would expect to see no warning messages, but if we ignore `--no-warnings` then that would not be the case.

We **could** filter out all of the arguments that are allowed in the [`NODE_OPTIONS`](https://nodejs.org/api/cli.html#node_optionsoptions) environment variable, and then spawn the child process with that environment variable. It wouldn't handle all Node.js flags, and we'd have to be careful not to overwrite any existing `NODE_OPTIONS`, and it would change `process.execArgv` which some code could be depending on.

Longer term, to properly support this, I think we need to be able to start the Deno CLI in Node mode. npm module support is getting us closer, but there are still some missing edge cases I think.

