The issue is the code in eslint-plugin-jsdoc does:

```
Object.defineProperty(exports, "__esModule", {
  value: true
});
var _default = {
  ...
};
exports.default = _default;
module.exports = exports.default;
```

So the final `module.exports` assignment actually cancels out all the previous exports defined on `exports`, but the cjs export analysis doesn't take that into account and it should. This will require an update in deno_ast to make the cjs export analysis a little smarter.

