Is what I've resorted to now. Proper solution would be neat.

Deno doesn't implement a service-worker runtime, so a dedicated `serviceworker` lib isn't really in scope — code using `ServiceWorkerGlobalScope` runs in a browser/other host, not Deno itself. The clean workaround, which still works, is:

```ts
/// <reference no-default-lib="true" />
/// <reference lib="webworker" />
declare const self: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope;
```

`self` then narrows to `ServiceWorkerGlobalScope` and type-checking passes. Closing as out of scope; happy to revisit if Deno gains native service-worker support.

