This has since been fixed. On current Deno, `data:` URI imports (including dynamic ones) are not added to the lockfile and are not integrity-checked — only real dependencies (jsr/npm/https) are locked and validated.

Repro with a lockfile present:

```ts
import { encodeBase64 } from "jsr:@std/encoding@1/base64";
const m = await import("data:text/javascript,export const x = 42");
console.log(encodeBase64("ok"), m.x);
```

The generated `deno.lock` contains only the `jsr:` specifier — no `data:` entry — and the run succeeds, matching the documented behavior. Closing as resolved; please reopen if you still hit this.

